dc_title_s: Iberian Peninsula 1:250,000: Castelo Branco, sheet 48. Series A.M.S. M581
dc_description_s: United States. Army Map Service. North Decimal Degree 40.0000. South Decimal Degree 39.0000. East Decimal Degree -7.0000. West Decimal Degree -8.0000. Alternate title: Castelo Branco, Portugal, Spain. Polyconic projection. With Spanish-English and Portuguese-English glossary. Relief shown by 100 m. contour interval, gradient tint and spot heights. Standard map series designation: A.M.S. M581. "Portugal, 1:50,000, Servicos Geodesicos, 1901-36; Portugal, 1:100,000, Instituto Geografico, sheet 25, 1935; Portugal, 1:100,000, Servicos Geodesicos, 1866-81; Portugal, 1:250,000, Estador Maior do Exercito, 1935-37; Spain, 1:50,000, Instituto Geografico, undated and 1926-28; Spain, 1:100,000, Estado Mayor, sheets 181, 1922, and 199, 1919; Spain, 1:200,000, Cuartel General del Generalisimo, undated and 1916-36. Spain, 1:200,000, Instituto Geografico, PROVINCIA de BADANOS, 1903; Road Map of Spain and Portugal, 1:400,000, AMS, sheet 46, Third Edition, 1943; Railways of Spain and Portugal 1:1,500,000, G.S.G.S., 1941, corrected from Intelligence Reports, 1942-43.".
